## 🔐 How the Cryptography Works

```
Your Document (any file)
        │
        ├──► SHA-256 hash ─────────────────── 64-char fingerprint
        │    (industry standard, one-way)
        │
        ├──► SHA3-256 hash ────────────────── 64-char fingerprint
        │    (Keccak, next-gen)
        │
        ├──► HMAC-SHA256 (+ secret key) ───── authenticated signature
        │    (only our system can produce this)
        │
        └──► Document ID ──────────────────── DG-XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
             SHA256(hash + filename + secret)
```

Any file modification — even changing one character — produces a **completely different hash**, making tampering instantly detectable.
